  <data name="TileHostEvent_FlyoutClosing" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Flyout window closing event. When the flyout window is about to close, the tile can decide whether to close it. Passes the Flyout's sender and the flyout's client area element.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_FlyoutInit" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Flyout window initialization event. When the user opens the flyout, this event is triggered, passing the flyout's client area element.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_FlyoutResize" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Flyout window size changed event. Passes the flyout window size and client area size.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_FlyoutShow" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Flyout window load event. When the user opens the flyout, this event is raised after the flyout is loaded, passing the flyout's client area element.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_Properties" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show property window event. When the user selects "Properties" from the tile's context menu, this event requests the property window. The tile may need to implement this. Note: The property window must be destroyed before unload.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_Resize" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Size changed event. Passes the tile's overall size and client area size.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_SidebarDirectionChanged" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Sidebar direction changed event. Fires when the sidebar is moved to the left or right side. Generally tiles do not need to respond unless required. Note: This is a pure position change, not a text direction change.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TileHostEvent_ThemeChanged" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The theme change event will pass in the new theme name. Tiles can automatically switch themes based on the theme name.</value>
  </data>
